Hi there,

> Now again we try to use cross-validation in GridSearchCV phase. Let's say cv = 5 (as in the doc example), how can we apply 5 folds on the same training dataset? The dataset has been split into 2-folds for StackingCVClassifier.

when I understand the question correctly, you are concerned about the GridSearchCV splitting the training set (already split by the StackingCVClassifier) further? Note that the order would be a bit different. It would first be split by GridSearchCV and then by the StackingCVClassifier. E.g,. if you use the StackingCVClassifier (say cv=2) and GridsearchCV (say cv=5), the iterations would look as follows:

```
for parameter setting in GridSearchCV iterator:
    for i in range(5):
        pass 4/5 of the dataset to the StackingCVClassifier
        for j in range(2):
            fit meta classifier on 1/2 of the 4/5th of the dataset (i.e, 2/5 of the orig training dataset)
```

