To set the back end pool using the config command use this ->

azure vmss config load-balancer-backend-address-pools set --parameter-file virtualMachineScaleSetsCreateOrUpdate_createOrUpdate.json --index 0 --ip-configurations-index 0 --network-interface-configurations-index 0 --value "test"

The reason you have to provide indexes is because back end address pool is 3 level below in the ip configurations..

"networkInterfaceConfigurations": [
        {
          "name": "",
          "primary": null,
          "ipConfigurations": [
            {
              "name": "",
              "subnet": {
                "id": ""
              },
              "applicationGatewayBackendAddressPools": [
                {
                  "id": ""
                }
              ],
              "loadBalancerBackendAddressPools": [
                "test"
              ]

You will see the usage if you do the following.

azure vmss config load-balancer-backend-address-pools set "test" --parameter-file virtualMachineScaleSetsCreateOrUpdate_createOrUpdate.json -h

The actually tells you all the index you need to set.

